h1.title-section Navbars
.gs-wrap
  p Hagrid Navbars

  h5 Table properties Navbars
  table.table-documentation
    thead
      tr
        th.first-col Property Details
        th Variations
        th Description
    tr
      th.first-col
        ul.list-documentation.list-documentation-details
          li.list__title
            b Dropdown
          li Type: class
          li Supports:&nbsp;
            b [types, sizes, looks, events]

          li.list__cta
            a(href="#dropdowns-example", class="btn btn-info btn-sm btn-block") Examples

      td
        ul.list-documentation.list-documentation-variations
          li
            b Sizes: m-[10-100]
            span e.g: m-10, m-20, m-30...
            pre
              code(class="language-html", prism)
                :code
                  <div class="m-10">...</div>
          li
            b Axis: m-{x, y}
            span e.g: m-10-x, m-20-y
            pre
              code(class="language-html", prism)
                :code
                  <div class="m-10-x">...</div>
          li
            b Sides: m-{top, right, bottom, left}
            span e.g: m-10-top, m-20-right, m-30-bottom
            pre
              code(class="language-html", prism)
                :code
                  <div class="m-10-top">...</div>
          li
            b Measurements: m-{px, percent, em, rem}
            span e.g: m-percent, m-em, m-rem
            pre
              code(class="language-html", prism)
                :code
                  <div class="m-10 m-em">...</div>
          li
            b Combined: sizes, axes, measurements
            span e.g: class="m-10-x m-10-top m-percent"
            pre
              code(class="language-html", prism)
                :code
                  <div class="m-10-x m-10-top m-percent">...</div>


      td Hagrid supports margin classes to separate elements, <b>.m-[sizes]</b> to specify a size, <b>.m-{measurements}</b> to specify the measurement, by default measurements is px, <b>.m-{axis}</b> to specify a axes and <b>.m-[side]</b> to specify a side.
